First reviewer asked about the differences between rows and columns in Design Structure Matrices (DSMs) \
Actually, design decisions are disposed both in rows and columns. A 'x' mark in use case model row / feature model column means that decisions related to the use case model depend on decisions about\
 the variability space (feature models). Therefore, each 'x' mark is derived from the need of communication between these design decisions (which may also be reflected in SPL artifacts).\
