The proposed approach was compared against PLUC and PLUSS techniques.They present important contributions \
for representing variability in use case models. However, both PLUC and PLUSS are not concerned with a modular design (a clear separation between variability artifacts and traditional software artifacts). In this way, the SPL evolvability is compromised. One of the contributions of this paper is to reveal this problem in the context of use case scenarios. However, the same problem occurs in other SPL models. \
