> How significant are these results on these examples?\
\
The second reviewer asked about the significance of quantitative analysis. In the first case study, Multimedia Message Product Line, we can realize a significant improvement in several metrics. For instance, the mean value of feature diffusion over use cases in PLUC and PLUSS was equal to 3.5. In our approach, this value was dropped to 2.  This means that, if the behavior related to one feature change,it might be required to review 3.5 use cases (in avarage). On the other hand, by applying our approach in this product line, it will be expected to review 2 use cases. The differences was not so significant in the Pedagogical Product Line (PPL), since its features are not spread in several use cases (as explained in Section 4.2.2). So, the main benefits in PPL were related to reduction in the specification size.\
